snippet.textDisplay:
What I managed to catch of the audio (parenthesis indicates sections I'm really unsure about):
Orb: "(Doom) is here. I have failed, brother. We have all failed. These (deities? domities? Really unsure about this one) defy all touch. You must return. Break your seal. Impossible. We will never survive. You must take them."
Inquisitor: "Return your men immediately!"
Orb: "At last."
Inquisitor: (I don't know what he's saying, but he's clearly mumbling during the scene where he's turning towards the marine. I suspect he might be just speaking in tongues, because the last few syllables are both quite clear and completely indecipherable.)

From this, I think we can construct a solid picture of what's happening. What the Orb is first showing the Inquisitor is a vision of a conversation, one between two Astartes. Probably something like this:
Brother 1: Doom is here. I have failed, brother.
Brother 2: We have all failed. These deities defy all touch.
Brother 1: You must return. Break your seal.
Brother 2: Impossible. We'll never survive. You must take them.

The implications of this conversation are clear: it is a vision of the future, one in which the Astartes on the planet are about to get into serious trouble. The Inquisitor, panicked, immediately turns to the Astartes to warn them of the implications of the vision, which is just enough distraction for the orb to possess him and draw power from him. Tragically, in trying to prevent the future described by the vision, the Inquisitor has only managed to ensure it comes to pass.
